<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 05 at 12:38PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORMS WILL AFFECT WESTERN FRANKLIN COUNTY
THROUGH 115 PM EDT...
At 1237 PM EDT, a Thunderstorm was located near Callaway, or near
Copper Hill. The thunderstorm is nearly stationary.
Pea size hail is possible with this shower along with very heavy
rainfall.
Locations impacted include...
Boones Mill...
Wirtz...
and Callaway.
Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</description>
